(firstQuint)Combination of Anti-PD-L1 and NK Immunotherapy for Recurrent Solid Tumors.

 By enrolling patients with solid tumors adapted to enrolled criteria, this study will document for the first time the safety and the short and long term efficacy of the combined therapy using anti-PD-L1 and natural killer (NK) cells.

 The safety will be evaluated by statistics of adverse reactions.

 The efficacy will be evaluated according to local relief degree, progress free survival (PFS) and overall survival (OS).

